<TITLE> Law adviser okay after road accident </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Khagrachhari, June 27 (bdnews24.com)Law adviser Hassan Ariff was involved in a road accident returning to Chittagong from a political dialogue session in Khagrachhari Friday. After receiving first aid treatment, he told reporters that he was well and would be able to attend both segments of the regional dialogue in Chittagong Saturday. Police said that the car carrying the adviser lost control and skidded into a roadside ditch when it reached the Mohamoni crossing in Manikchhari around 4pm. Hassan Ariff's personal assistant Hamidur Rahman, bodyguard Abdul Khaleque, and driver Md Ibrahim were also injured in the accident and all were admitted to Chittagong Medical College Hospital. Hamidur Rahman said that police and locals first took them to Manikchhari Health Complex and then to the CMCH. Colonel AKM Fariduzzaman, director of Chittagong Medical College Hospital, said the adviser and the three others were out of danger; their injuries were minor. Adviser Hassan Ariff was later taken to a private clinic named Cardicare where commerce adviser Hossain Zillur Rahman's younger brother Dr Mohsin Zillur examined him. "I am well. I will be able to attend both parts of the dialogue," the adviser told reporters on leaving the clinic. Hassan Ariff was attending a dialogue session with tribal communities in Khagrachhari. Communications adviser Ghulam Quader also went to Khagrachhari for talks with the indigenous people. bdnews24.com/c
